{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769622662,"nonce":"NUgKE319FiAxJgOaL29AkelQKHQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87meBCt","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/103","origin":"github"},"title":"Improve workspace to enforce workflow protocol compliance","message":"## Problem\nEven when agents know the rules, it's easy to violate the workflow protocol. Recent example: I created `.agent/GLOSSARY.md` directly on `main` branch without:\n1. Checking for existing issues first\n2. Creating an issue before starting work\n3. Creating a feature branch before making changes\n\n## Root Cause\nThe workspace relies on agents remembering the protocol rather than enforcing it through tooling.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### 1. Pre-commit Hook: Prevent Direct Commits to Main\n**What**: Git hook that blocks commits to `main` branch\n**Why**: Forces agents to use feature branches\n**Implementation**: Add to `.agent/hooks/pre-commit`\n```bash\nif [ \"$(git branch --show-current)\" = \"main\" ]; then\n  echo \"ERROR: Direct commits to main are forbidden\"\n  echo \"Create a feature branch: git checkout -b feature/ISSUE-\u003cnumber\u003e-description\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n### 2. Agent Reminder Checklist\n**What**: Prominent checklist at top of `.agent/AI_RULES.md`\n**Why**: Visual reminder of mandatory first steps\n**Implementation**:\n```markdown\n## Before Starting ANY Work\n- [ ] Check GitHub issues for existing work\n- [ ] Verify git identity is configured\n- [ ] Check current branch (should NOT be main)\n- [ ] Create/assign issue if needed\n- [ ] Run `start_issue_work.sh` to create feature branch + work plan\n```\n\n### 3. Workflow Script Discoverability\n**What**: Make `start_issue_work.sh` easier to find/use\n**Why**: Script exists but agents may not know to use it\n**Implementation**:\n- Add to README.md quick start\n- Create alias: `make start-issue ISSUE=100`\n- Add to `.agent/CLI_COMMANDS.md`\n\n### 4. Issue Templates\n**What**: GitHub issue templates for common task types\n**Why**: Makes creating well-formed issues faster\n**Implementation**: `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`\n- `feature.md` - New feature template\n- `bug.md` - Bug report template\n- `workspace.md` - Workspace improvement template\n\n## Success Criteria\n- [ ] Pre-commit hook blocks commits to main\n- [ ] AI_RULES.md has prominent checklist\n- [ ] `start_issue_work.sh` documented in README and CLI_COMMANDS\n- [ ] Issue templates created\n\n## Priority\n**High** - This is foundational for multi-agent coordination\n\n## Related\n- WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md - Task coordination rules\n- AI_RULES.md - Core workflow\n- `.agent/rules/common/git-hygiene.md` - Git workflow requirements","files":null}]}